  <div class="region-inner region-content-inner">
    <a id="main-content"></a>
            		<h1 class="title" id="page-title">Riot fights back against SOPA</h1>
                        <div class="block block-system block-main block-system-main odd block-without-title" id="block-system-main">
  <div class="block-inner clearfix">
                
    <div class="content clearfix">
      


<article about="/articles/20140910/502/riot-fights-back-against-sopa" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document" class="node node-article node-published node-not-promoted node-not-sticky self-posted author- odd clearfix" id="node-article-502">
        <span property="dc:title" content="Riot fights back against SOPA" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><span property="sioc:num_replies" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>	  
    
    <div class="post-date">Posted on 01-11-12</div>		
		<div class="share-bar">
			<a class="print_ico" href="/print/articles/20140910/502/riot-fights-back-against-sopa">Print</a>
			<!-- <a class="pdf_ico" href="/printpdf/articles/20140910/502/riot-fights-back-against-sopa">PDF</a> -->
			<span class='st_email_custom st_ico' displayText='Email'></span>
			<span class='st_twitter_custom st_ico' displayText='Tweet'></span>
			<span class='st_facebook_custom st_ico' displayText='Facebook'></span>
			<span class='st_linkedin_custom st_ico' displayText='LinkedIn'></span>
			<span class='st_google_custom st_ico' displayText='Google'></span>
			<script type="text/javascript">var switchTo5x=true;</script>
			<script type="text/javascript" src="http://w.sharethis.com/button/buttons.js"></script>
			<script type="text/javascript">
				stLight.options({
		        publisher: 'f65a6e51-8a93-4acd-a665-976809c16a17',
		        onhover: false
		    });</script>
		</div>

    
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-field-main-image field-type-image field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://www.riotgames.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/content/article/images/main/StopSOPA.jpg?itok=j4TL5iri" width="700" height="300" alt="Uncle Ryze wants YOU to stop SOPA." /></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"> <p>As challengers of convention, we really don&rsquo;t like bureaucracy here at Riot Games. So when we heard that some buzzkill lawmakers had a bill before the House of Representatives called the Stop Online Piracy Act (or SOPA for short) that jeopardized players&rsquo; rights, we felt compelled to get involved. After all there are a lot of players producing free content for the community.</p>
<p>While <em>League of Legends</em> wasn&rsquo;t directly in SOPA&rsquo;s line of fire, it put our growing community of streamers, fan artists, and YouTubers at risk of getting shut down or even winding up in trouble with the law. It could also have potentially left the <em>LoL</em> forums subject to censorship. That&rsquo;s a lot of crappy red tape we&rsquo;d rather do without, so we set about arming players with the info they needed to oppose the bill.</p>
<p>Step one was pointing players to their local representatives to express their opinions. Our Cofounder <a href="http://na.leagueoflegends.com/board/showthread.php?t=1696462" target="_blank">Brandon &ldquo;Ryze&rdquo; Beck kicked things off with an informative post on the forums</a> that detailed the potential havoc SOPA could wreak on the <em>League of Legends</em> community. &nbsp;He was even <a href="http://na.leagueoflegends.com/board/showthread.php?t=1696462&amp;highlight=#post19572246" target="_blank">backed up by Colorado State Representative (and summoner) Jared Polis</a>, who stopped in to lend his expert opinion. We also put Riot Games council Logan &ldquo;Brolaf&rdquo; Margulies on the case to answer community questions at <a href="http://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/oco15/iama_attorney_for_riot_games_directing_our/" target="_blank">one of our first reddit AMAs</a>.</p>
<p>Ultimately, SOPA was defeated by a strong showing of opposition by the Internet community, and a group of vocal protest organizations. We&rsquo;re proud to have been a part of helping to keep the Internet free from bullshit red tape.</p>
 </div></div></div>
        
    <span class="print-link"></span><div class="field-group-format group_tags field-group-div group-tags clearfix speed-none effect-none"><h3><span>Tags:</span></h3><div class="field
